body:
I'm using `jest` coupled with `Testutils` to test my `react` code.
Just check the following code.

``` js
//All the variables surfix with Node are DOMElement
 nameFieldNode.value='tmp';    //initial value is not 'tmp'
 indexFieldNode.value='indext';    //initial value is not 'indext'
 TestUtils.Simulate.change(nameFieldNode);  
 TestUtils.Simulate.change(indexFieldNode);
 expect(nameFieldNode.value).toBe('tmp');
 expect(indexFieldNode.value).toBe('indext');
```

With the above snippet, The second expect would fail and you can see that the value of indexFieldNode is not updated at all.

So I change the code to make it like this.

``` js
//All the variables surfix with Node are DOMElement
 nameFieldNode.value='tmp';    //initial value is not 'tmp'
 TestUtils.Simulate.change(nameFieldNode);  
 indexFieldNode.value='indext';    //initial value is not 'indext'
 TestUtils.Simulate.change(indexFieldNode);
 expect(nameFieldNode.value).toBe('tmp');
 expect(indexFieldNode.value).toBe('indext');
```

This time, everything works properly.
